Class NoOpCasAttributeEncoder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apereo.cas.authentication.support.NoOpCasAttributeEncoder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CasAttributeEncoder

    @RefreshScope
 @Component(value="noOpCasAttributeEncoder")
public class NoOpCasAttributeEncoder
extends java.lang.Object
implements CasAttributeEncoder
    This is NoOpCasAttributeEncoder that does no encoding of attributes received. It will simply return the same exact collection of attributes received back to the caller.

    5.0.0

      • encodeAttributes

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> encodeAttributes(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> attributes,
                                                                         Service service)
        Description copied from interface: CasAttributeEncoder
        Encodes attributes that are ready to be released. Specifically, this method tries to ensure that the PGT and the credential password are correctly encrypted before they are released. Attributes should not be filtered and removed and it is assumed that all will be returned back to the service.
        Specified by:
        encodeAttributes in interface CasAttributeEncoder
        Parameters:
        attributes - The attribute collection that is ready to be released
        service - the requesting service for which attributes are to be encoded
        Returns:
        collection of attributes after encryption ready for release.
